Nigeria’s anti-graft agency, Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC), has arrested a suspect on the watch-list of the US Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI), Kelechi Vitalis Anozie, wanted for wire fraud. Anozie, who is the founder of Praying City Church located in Owerri, Imo State, was arrested in Enugu. EFCC spokesperson, Wilson Uwujaren, said: “operatives of the Enugu zonal command of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission arrested Kelechi Vitalis Anozie, a suspect on the watch list of the US Federal Bureau of Investigation, FBI on March 10, 2022, following credible intelligence linking him to alleged conspiracy, wire fraud and money laundering. “Anozie and four other suspects: Valentine Iro, Ekene Ekechukwu (alias Ogedi Power), Bright Azubuike (alias Bright Bauer Azubuike) and Ifeanyi Junior, are alleged to have defrauded one F.F who lives in Illinois, United States, the sum of $135,800 US Dollars and another $47,000.”